<i>adverb</i>: 항시 [항시], 항상 [항상], 으레 [으레], 언제나 [언ː제나], 언제 [언ː제], 밤낮없이 [밤나덥씨], 밤낮 [밤낟], 매양 [매양], 늘 [늘], 노상 [노상] <i>noun</i>: 상시 [상시], 사철 [사ː철], 사시사철 [사ː시사ː철] <i>pronoun</i>: 언제 [언ː제] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>항시 [항시]</dt><br>
<dd>always; all the time; at all times</dd><br>
<dd>똑같은 상태로 언제나.</dd><br>
<dd>Always in the same state.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>항상 [항상]</dt><br>
<dd>always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>어느 때에나 변함없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Invariably at any time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>으레 [으레]</dt><br>
<dd>1. as a matter of course</dd><br>
<dd>두말할 것 없이 당연히.</dd><br>
<dd>Naturally, needless to say.</dd><br>
<dd>2. always; invariably; without fail</dd><br>
<dd>언제나 늘.</dd><br>
<dd>Every time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언제나 [언ː제나]</dt><br>
<dd>1. always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>어느 때에나. 또는 때에 따라 달라지지 않고 변함없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Every time; invariably without changing with time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. when</dd><br>
<dd>어느 때가 되어야.</dd><br>
<dd>At what time.</dd><br>
<dd>3. at all times</dd><br>
<dd>아무 때에나.</dd><br>
<dd>At any time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언제 [언ː제]</dt><br>
<dd>1. when; at what time</dd><br>
<dd>알지 못하는 어느 때에.</dd><br>
<dd>At some time one does not know.</dd><br>
<dd>2. some time; someday</dd><br>
<dd>분명히 정해지지 않은 미래의 어느 때에.</dd><br>
<dd>At some time in the future that is not decided.</dd><br>
<dd>3. always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>아무 때에. 아무 때나.</dd><br>
<dd>At any time; whenever.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>밤낮없이 [밤나덥씨]</dt><br>
<dd>always; around the clock</dd><br>
<dd>밤이나 낮이나 가리지 않고 항상.</dd><br>
<dd>All the time; days and nights.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>밤낮 [밤낟]</dt><br>
<dd>always; around the clock</dd><br>
<dd>밤과 낮을 가리지 않고 늘.</dd><br>
<dd>All the time; days and nights.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>매양 [매양]</dt><br>
<dd>always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>매 때마다.</dd><br>
<dd>Every time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>늘 [늘]</dt><br>
<dd>1. always</dd><br>
<dd>언제나 변함이 없이 항상.</dd><br>
<dd>Invariably, all the time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. often</dd><br>
<dd>평소에 자주.</dd><br>
<dd>Frequently, in ordinary times.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>노상 [노상]</dt><br>
<dd>always</dd><br>
<dd>언제나 변함없이 줄곧.</dd><br>
<dd>Invariably all the time.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>상시 [상시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>일상적으로 늘.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of always being.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ordinary times</dd><br>
<dd>특별한 일이 없는 보통 때.</dd><br>
<dd>Ordinary times, times in which nothing special is happening.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사철 [사ː철]</dt><br>
<dd>1. four seasons</dd><br>
<dd>봄, 여름, 가을, 겨울의 네 계절.</dd><br>
<dd>Four seasons, namely, spring, summer, fall, and winter.</dd><br>
<dd>2. always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>늘 변함이 없이 한결같음.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being consistent, without any change.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사시사철 [사ː시사ː철]</dt><br>
<dd>four seasons; being throughout the year; being all year round; always</dd><br>
<dd>봄, 여름, 가을, 겨울 네 계절 내내의 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>A period from spring, summer, fall and through winter.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>pronoun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언제 [언ː제]</dt><br>
<dd>1. when; what time</dd><br>
<dd>알지 못하는 어느 때.</dd><br>
<dd>Some time that one does not know.</dd><br>
<dd>2. once</dd><br>
<dd>과거의 어느 때.</dd><br>
<dd>The time of the past.</dd><br>
<dd>3. any time; always</dd><br>
<dd>특별히 정해지지 않은 어느 때.</dd><br>
<dd>Some indefinite time.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>